.SH "OPTIONS"
.sp
\fB\-a\fP \fIn\fP, \fB\-\-article\-width\fP=\fIn\fP
.RS 4
Set the article width in Reader Mode to \fIn\fP columns.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-categories\fP=\fIlist\fP
.RS 4
Set the categories in the header.
Available categories: top, best, new, ask, show, favorites.
Separate categories with comma.
The first category is the view shown on launch; it appears as the \fBclx\fP logo in the header rather than as a named tab.
Default: "top,best,ask,show,favorites".
.RE
.sp
\fB\-c\fP \fIn\fP, \fB\-\-comment\-width\fP=\fIn\fP
.RS 4
Set the comment width to \fIn\fP columns.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-d, \-\-disable\-history\fP
.RS 4
Disable marking stories as read.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-indent\fP=\fIn\fP
.RS 4
Set the comment section indent size to \fIn\fP spaces per nesting level.
When the requested indent would shrink a comment\(cqs text column below a readable minimum, the indent plateaus and deeper comments share an ancestor\(cqs indent level while the depth\-colored bar continues to convey nesting.
Default: 1.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-n, \-\-nerdfonts\fP
.RS 4
Enable Nerd Fonts icons as decorators for some elements (requires a Nerd Font\-patched font).
Auto\-enabled for Ghostty, which embeds Nerd Fonts.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-pages\fP=\fIn\fP
.RS 4
Set the number of pages to fetch per category, between 1 and 5.
Higher values fetch more stories but increase load time.
Only applies to top, new and best.
Ask and show always fetch one page because their story pools are small (~150\-200 stories).
Default: 3.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-v, \-\-version\fP
.RS 4
Show the current version of \fBcircumflex\fP.
.RE
.SH "COMMANDS"
.sp
\fBclx add\fP [\fIID\fP]
.RS 4
Add item to list of favorites by \fIID\fP.
.RE
.sp
\fBclx article\fP [\fIID\fP]
.RS 4
Go directly to Reader Mode for a given item \fIID\fP without first going through the main view.
.RE
.sp
\fBclx comments\fP [\fIID\fP]
.RS 4
Go directly to the comment section for a given item \fIID\fP without first going through the main view.
.RE
.sp
\fBclx url\fP [\fIURL\fP]
.RS 4
Open a URL directly in Reader Mode.
.RE
.sp
\fBclx clear\fP
.RS 4
Clear the history of visited items.
.RE
.sp
\fBclx default\-theme\fP
.RS 4
Generate a starter theme file in the config directory.
See \fBFILES\fP.
.RE
.SH "HISTORY"
.sp
\fBcircumflex\fP tracks which stories you have visited.
Visited stories are dimmed in the list.
When returning to a comment section, comments posted since your last visit are highlighted with a new\-comment indicator.
.sp
Use \fBclx clear\fP to reset history, or \fB\-\-disable\-history\fP to turn tracking off entirely.
.SH "FAVORITES"
.sp
Press \fIf\fP to add the currently highlighted submission to your list of favorites.
Remove submissions from the Favorites page with \fIx\fP.
.sp
The favorites file is pretty\-printed JSON, suitable for hand\-editing or version control.
.SH "ENVIRONMENT"
.sp
\fBXDG_CONFIG_HOME\fP, \fBXDG_CACHE_HOME\fP
.RS 4
Override the directories where \fBcircumflex\fP stores its config and cache files.
See \fBFILES\fP for what lives where.
.RE
.sp
\fBCLX_BROWSER\fP
.RS 4
Command used to open URLs (article links and comment pages).
The URL is appended as the final argument.
For example, \f(CRCLX_BROWSER="firefox \-\-new\-tab"\fP opens links in a new Firefox tab.
When unset, the platform default opener is used (\fBopen\fP on macOS, \fBxdg\-open\fP on Linux, \fBrundll32\fP on Windows).
.RE
.SH "FILES"
.sp
\fI$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/circumflex/theme.toml\fP
.RS 4
TOML color theme.
Run \fBclx default\-theme\fP to write a starter file pre\-populated with every key and its default value.
Values may be named colors (\f(CRred\fP, \f(CRbright_blue\fP, .\|.\|.), hex strings (\f(CR#ff8800\fP), or ANSI 256 indices (\f(CR0\fP\-\f(CR255\fP).
Unrecognized values render with no styling.
.RE
.sp
\fI$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/circumflex/favorites.json\fP
.RS 4
Saved favorites.
.RE
.sp
\fI$XDG_CACHE_HOME/circumflex/history.json\fP
.RS 4
IDs of visited stories.
.RE
.sp
When the XDG variables are unset, the platform defaults apply: \f(CR~/Library/Application Support/circumflex/\fP and \f(CR~/Library/Caches/circumflex/\fP on macOS; \f(CR~/.config/circumflex/\fP and \f(CR~/.cache/circumflex/\fP on Linux.
